---
import Layout from "../../components/layout/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Privacy information for Open Ordinal."
  lang="en"
  canonical="https://openordinal.org/legal/privacy"
>
  <section class="archive-shell entry-prose">
    <h1 class="text-[46px] leading-tight text-ink">Privacy</h1>

    <p class="ui-meta text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-dim">Last updated: 2026-03-18</p>

    <h2>Scope</h2>
    <p>This policy describes how Open Ordinal handles personal data when you visit the site or subscribe to newsletter updates.</p>

    <h2>Data controller</h2>
    <p>Open Ordinal is operated by Utopia UGX Group Ltd. Privacy requests: <a href="mailto:hello@openordinal.org">hello@openordinal.org</a>.</p>

    <h2>What we process</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Anonymous traffic analytics including page views, referrers, browser and device metadata, and aggregate visit measurements through our self-hosted Umami instance</li>
      <li>Newsletter subscription data (email address and related subscription metadata) through Buttondown</li>
      <li>Operational logs generated by Cloudflare Pages as part of standard hosting and delivery</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>This site does not use analytics or advertising cookies. Our self-hosted Umami setup is configured for cookieless traffic measurement.</p>

    <h2>Legal bases</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Consent for newsletter subscription and delivery</li>
      <li>Basic anonymous traffic measurement, service security, and abuse prevention</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Newsletter records are retained until you unsubscribe or request deletion</li>
      <li>Anonymous analytics data are retained according to our Umami retention settings</li>
      <li>Infrastructure logs are retained according to Cloudflare's retention settings</li>
      <li>Support correspondence is retained as needed for request resolution</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Processors and sharing</h2>
    <p>We use third-party processors to run the service, including Cloudflare Pages (hosting and delivery) and Buttondown (newsletter), and we operate a self-hosted Umami instance for anonymous analytics. We do not sell personal data.</p>

    <h2>International processing</h2>
    <p>Service providers may process data in multiple jurisdictions. Your data may be processed outside your country.</p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, restrict, port, or object to your data. You may withdraw newsletter consent at any time by unsubscribing.</p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this page as the service evolves. Material changes will be reflected by updating the date above.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
